encount_battle_default.mission_info: These guys are a real pain... Fine, I'll take them on.

coyote_g01_010.mission_info: Never judge a book by its cover. Let's tail Kosuke-kun and find out just what type of guy he is.

coyote_g01_030.mission_info: Scaling walls is my specialty. Plenty of footings, too. Time to strut my stuff.

coyote_btl01_010.mission_info: I can't believe I got duped by this idiot. Don't wanna cause a scene, so I better shut him up!

coyote_g01_040.mission_info: Kosuke-kun's supposedly in the tatami room on the 5th floor. The entire building's on high alert after my presence became known. Can't afford getting caught now.

coyote_btl01_030.mission_info: I have no business with these guys from the tatami room, but if they wanna fight, who am I to turn them down?

coyote_g01_050.mission_info: Seeing him run only makes me want to chase after him harder. Hey, hold up!

coyote_m01_01100.mission_info: I can't take Keiko-san to that bar. I'll have her lie low at Genda-sensei's place for a bit.

coyote_m01_01300.mission_info: Genda-sensei's here all alone. Maybe Saori-san and Hoshino-kun aren't here because they're on a big case or something. I wonder...

coyote_m01_01500.mission_info: Time to meet up with Kaito-san and get Keiko-san's money back from that shady bar owner, who's supposedly ex-Tojo.

coyote_btl01_050.mission_info: These brats go around pissing people off and record it on their phones? That's a problem. Punks like this need to be punished.

coyote_m01_02100.mission_info: Let's head back to Yagami Detective Agency. Gonna have to call up Sugiura and Tsukumo when I do.

coyote_m01_02200.mission_info: Wait... what was I supposed to do when I got back? It's times like these when I turn to my trusty partner, Kaito-san.

coyote_m01_02350.mission_info: Time to get some rest. The couch in my office is nice and comfy for sleeping on, even if it looks a little dirty.

coyote_m01_02400.mission_info: It's been a while since I last saw Tsukumo and Sugiura. Can't believe they teamed up to start a detective agency. Kind of excited to see what sort of place they're running.

coyote_btl01_060.mission_info: Kind of unseemly to take on these kids, but I'm toast if I get caught here. Fortunately, they're all nasty punks, so I don't have to hold back!

coyote_m01_02900.mission_info: Yokohama's known for its Chinatown. Not bad. We're about to discuss the job the guys have for us at a restaurant called Kyoinro. I think they said the client's a high school chairman.

coyote_m01_03300.mission_info: Yokohama's no joke. Chinatown was awesome. I should rest and prep for tomorrow. The couch at Yokohama 99 looks plenty comfy, too.

coyote_m01_03700.mission_info: Gotta set up the spy cameras, but this place is huge. Time to put my detective's eye to use and discreetly find good spots for them.

coyote_m01_04600.mission_info: I finished setting up the cameras. Time to meet up with Tsukumo in the gym to discuss our next move.

coyote_m01_04800.mission: Head to Class 2-2 on the 2nd Floor
coyote_m01_04800.mission_info: Class 2-2 is where that girl was bullied. It's on the second floor of the classroom building. Better see what's going on with my own eyes.

coyote_g01_070.mission_info: Need to check up on the girl who was being bullied. But I can't forget, we're just AC repairmen right now. No one can know we've been watching through hidden cameras.

coyote_m01_05000.mission: Go to the Chairman's Office on the 3rd Floor
coyote_m01_05000.mission_info: How will the chairman react after he learns about the bullying? His office is on the 3rd floor of the east building. Let's head over right away.

coyote_m01_05200.mission: Check the Camera by the 2nd Floor Staircase
coyote_m01_05200.mission_info: Is the camera I just set up already malfunctioning? I'm passing by the 2nd floor staircase, anyway, so might as well check on it real quick.

coyote_g01_080.mission_info: Crap, if I get caught now, I'll be branded as a perv... Okay, Yagami. Get out of sight first, think later!

coyote_g01_090.mission: Head to Class 2-2 without Getting Spotted
coyote_g01_090.mission_info: I've seen the bullying for myself, so I'd better act sooner rather than later. Let's do what we need to do and split. I need to get to Class 2-2 without being seen so I can set up Tsukumo's speakers!

coyote_m01_05500.mission_info: Time to set up the speakers in the classroom. Where does Koda-san sit again?

coyote_M01_05750.mission_info: Tsukumo and the others managed to make it out of Seiryo High safely, right? I should head to Yokohama 99 myself and meet up with them.

coyote_m01_05850.mission_info: I put in some good work today. Let's rest up for tomorrow.

coyote_m01_05950.mission_info: We should be able to use the speakers I set up yesterday to put a stop to the bullying, but it's still risky. Anyhow, let's head to Seiryo High and find out.

coyote_btl01_020.mission_info: Trying to threaten me with the Tojo Clan? Not exactly the behavior of a model student.

coyote_btl01_040.mission: Defeat the Owner of the Shady Bar
coyote_btl01_040.mission_info: Figured talking was pointless. This ex-yakuza bastard tried to trick a girl and sell her off. I've got no reason to hold back!

coyote_m01_03450.mission_info: First job out in Ijincho. We're setting up hidden cameras around campus to see if there's any bullying going on. Let's take a taxi to Seiryo High.

coyote_g01_020.mission: Find a Way to Sneak into the Building
coyote_g01_020.mission_info: Why would Kosuke-kun be at such a shady place? It's the perfect chance to see his true colors. Now if I can just make my way in without getting spotted...

coyote_side_btl051_010.mission_info: The brats who've been making fun of Ebisu-sensei are attacking me now. Time for some student discipline.

coyote_side_btl051_020.mission_info: Ebisu-sensei is out of his mind with anger. His career will be over if he lays a hand on any of these students. I gotta calm him down!

coyote_side_g01_010.mission_info: Gotta catch suspicious guy and ask him some questions!

coyote_m02_00200.mission_info: Let's hear what the chairman has to say about Hiro Mikoshiba, the murdered student teacher.

coyote_m02_00300.mission_info: To think I'd have to interview Sawa-sensei... Hopefully this goes smoothly, considering our previous track record.

coyote_g02_010.mission_info: Guess I'll look around a little bit until she returns.

coyote_m02_00500.mission_info: I should see if anyone from the basketball club is on campus. They were the ones bullying Koda, and were close with Mikoshiba, apparently...

coyote_m02_00600.mission_info: Since Koda's part of the basketball club too, she might have some information about Mikoshiba. Wouldn't hurt to ask, anyway.

coyote_btl02_010.mission_info: Okay, we can talk after I show them what happens when you whip a basketball at my face!

coyote_m02_00750.mission: Look for an "In" at the School
coyote_m02_00750.mission_info: I really need to find a reason to be on campus so I can question people... I wonder if there are any staff openings? Maybe I'll ask at reception.

coyote_m02_00810.mission: Figure Out How to Get Out of This
coyote_m02_00810.mission_info: If I don't do something, this kid's gonna have the whole school think I'm a peeping tom... Let's just stay calm and figure out what her angle is.

coyote_m02_00830.mission_info: The Mystery Research Club, huh? If I became their advisor, I'd have a good reason to be on campus... Hopefully this test of hers isn't too outrageous.

coyote_m02_00840.mission_info: So, I have to infiltrate the dance club to get the MRC advisor gig. Apparently they practice in the gym basement... I better make sure this goes well.

coyote_m02_01000.mission_info: Apparently, Mikoshiba spent a lot of time with the basketball club while he was at Seiryo. Let's drop in on their practice and see what they have to say.

coyote_m02_01350.mission_info: Yeah, I highly doubt these brats are looking to make peace with me in an isolated part of the school... Let's see what pathetic trap they've set for me.

coyote_btl02_020.mission_info: The way they run their mouths tells me they're no saints. Guess there's no need to treat 'em like kids then!

coyote_m02_01600.mission_info: It sounds like Sawa-sensei's been giving mixed opinions of Mikoshiba. I should question her again.

coyote_m02_01900.mission_info: Well, I have even more questions for Sawa-sensei now. Apparently she's been called up to the chairman's office—I should head there now.

coyote_m02_01200.mission_info: Hmm, strange—nobody from the basketball club came to practice. I have a feeling something's wrong... Let's try and find Koda first.

coyote_m03_00400.mission_info: I've still got plenty of time before I meet with Sawa-sensei. Maybe I ought to check in at Yokohama 99 beforehand.

coyote_m03_00420.mission: Hit the Town and Test the New Toy
coyote_m03_00420.mission_info: Tsukumo always comes up with the most interesting gadgets. Time to try this Buzz Researcher out!

coyote_m03_00450.mission_info: I should report back to Tsukumo. I'm sure he'll be pleased to hear how the test run went.

coyote_m03_00600.mission_info: Time to see Sawa-sensei... Hopefully we're meeting outside the school because she's decided to open up about the truth.

coyote_btl03_010.mission_info: Who the hell are these guys!? I haven't even been in town that long, but they've definitely got a bone to pick with me!

coyote_btl03_020.mission_info: Why would a handyman see me as someone in his line of work...? Well, he started this fight, so I'm gonna finish it!

coyote_m03_01000.mission_info: Well, this turned out to be an awfully eventful day... Kaito-san and Sugiura are out for drinks with the handyman, so I'll chat with Tsukumo.

coyote_m04_00200.mission_info: Sawa-sensei seemed pretty freaked out last night. I should check on her and see if she's feeling any better...

coyote_m04_00600.mission_info: Sawa-sensei seemed pretty freaked out last night. I should check on her and see if she's feeling any better...

coyote_m04_00900.mission_info: Mikoshiba's body was found here in Ijincho... I bet the police already scoured the place, but I should still check out the scene—an abandoned building next to a park by Sakura River.

coyote_g04_010.mission_info: I should be able to sneak in from the back side. Point of entry's pretty high up, but I'll risk it for a lead in this case.

coyote_g04_030.mission_info: Who's been spying on us!? I'm not letting them get away!

coyote_m04_01800.mission_info: I've already learned a lot about this case, but I'm gonna need to go beyond Ijincho to find all the facts. Better head back to Yokohama 99.

coyote_m04_01900.mission_info: I'm inspecting the scene of Ehara's sexual harassment in Tokyo tomorrow. I'd better hit the hay.

coyote_m04_02050.mission: Take a Taxi to Ikebukuro Station
coyote_m04_02050.mission_info: I'm supposed to meet up with Hoshino-kun to inspect the scene of Ehara's sexual harassment. I should grab a cab and head to Ikebukuro Station.

coyote_m04_02600.mission_info: I visited the crime scenes to understand what I could about Hiro Mikoshiba and Akihiro Ehara... Now, I just need Sawa-sensei to tell me about what happened between Mikoshiba and Toshiro Ehara. Let's head to Seiryo High and find her.

coyote_m04_02900.mission_info: Tomorrow is finally the day we interview Ehara. I think we're ready for it. Let's go back to Yokohama 99 and rest up.

coyote_m04_03100.mission_info: Seems like the news about Ehara got picked up online... Time to talk to Tsukumo.

coyote_g04_070.mission_info: There you are, White Masks! These guys are the Ijincho gang known as the Yokohama Liumang. But what concerns me now is who hired them and why they're targeting me... I'll catch them and find out. You're not getting away!

coyote_btl04_010.mission_info: I thought I was chasing them down, but clearly I've been baited. This is the White Masks' lair... I might be in some trouble here!

coyote_btl04_020.mission_info: Having Kaito-san here is like having the strength of a hundred men. But the White Masks don't seem to know who hired them... which means there's no reason to stay here. Time to kick down anyone in our way and get the hell away.

coyote_m04_03350.mission_info: They damaged Tsukumo's office because they were targeting me. I should go back and apologize, at the very least.

coyote_m04_03500.mission: Rest on the Couch at Yokohama 99
coyote_m04_03500.mission_info: Damn, I can't believe they'd actually hurt Tsukumo and Sugiura! Ehara's accomplices seem to really hate me. Argh, and that reminds me, tomorrow is the interview with Ehara. I should rest up today.

coyote_m04_03750.mission_info: Gotta go to Kamurocho to see Saori-san. By the time we meet up, it'll be time to interview Ehara.

coyote_m04_03900.mission_info: I should head to Genda Law Office to see Saori-san. Then it'll be time to interview Ehara.

coyote_btl04_030.mission_info: Even in Kamurocho, you gotta have some manners when you ask people questions. I mean, you're not fit to be a detective in this town if you let these thugs have their way with you!

coyote_m04_04200.mission: Go to the Tokyo Detention Center Via Taxi
coyote_m04_04200.mission_info: Gotta catch a taxi to get to Ehara's interview at the Tokyo Detention Center.

coyote_m04_04500.mission: Return to the Yagami Detective Agency
coyote_m04_04500.mission_info: I think it's time to call it a day and head back to Yagami Detective Agency. Kaito-san will be there, and I can relax for a while.

coyote_m05_00200.mission_info: Video footage of Ehara murdering Mikoshiba has been released. Let's head to Genda Law Office and ask Saori to put together another meeting with Ehara.

coyote_m05_00600.mission_info: If this was all part of Ehara's plan, he's craftier than we expected. Let's head to Genda Law Office and ask Saori to put together another meeting with Ehara.

coyote_m05_00800.mission_info: Saori-san's looking up Yui Mamiya's home address for us. Kaito and I are gonna grab some grub in the meantime.

coyote_btl05_010.mission_info: Guess they aren't just curious about what we're up to... Isn't Kamurocho supposed to be more peaceful without the Tojo!?

coyote_m05_01200.mission_info: Kaito-san sure is dependable in times like this. Apparently, the club in the back of Theater Square's the private little hangout for those chumps.

coyote_g05_010.mission_info: I need to make sure Kaito-san's okay, but I can't let these guys see me sneaking around... Better be extra careful.

coyote_btl05_020.mission_info: I knew Kaito-san was in trouble back here. Let's clean up and exit stage right, quick!

coyote_m05_01700.mission_info: Time to try and get an interview with Yui Mamiya, Ehara's harassment victim. I need to meet up with Saori-san first.

coyote_m05_01750.mission: Take a Taxi to Mamiya's Apartment
coyote_m05_01750.mission_info: Time to try and get an interview with Yui Mamiya, Ehara's harassment victim. I should take a taxi to her apartment in East Ikebukuro.

coyote_m05_02100.mission: Talk to Saori and the Others
coyote_m05_02100.mission_info: Time to report Mamiya's statement to the rest of the team at Genda's office. Saori-san will be able to help with that.

coyote_m05_01000.mission: Get Away from Genda Law Office
coyote_m05_01000.mission_info: How long have these RK guys been watching us? In any case, we need to distance ourselves from Saori-san and the others for now.

coyote_m06_00200.mission: Hit the Couch at Yagami Detective Agency
coyote_m06_00200.mission_info: It's still just a theory at this point, but I feel like I'm getting real close to the heart of the matter... But it's time to call it a day and head back to the Yagami Detective Agency.

coyote_m06_00350.mission_info: All these Kurokawa Academy graduates keep popping up in Mikoshiba's murder case. I think it's likely Sawa-sensei is one of them. She's connected to Yui Mamiya somehow... I should go talk to her and see how she reacts to what I say. Time to head to Ijincho!

coyote_m06_00450.mission_info: All these Kurokawa Academy graduates keep popping up in Mikoshiba's murder case. I think it's likely Sawa-sensei is one of them. She's connected to Yui Mamiya somehow... I should go talk to her and see how she reacts to what I say. She's probably in the faculty room.

coyote_m06_00600.mission_info: Turns out Sawa-sensei and Yui Mamiya were connected after all... I can't wait to get out of this school and tell Saori-san about this.

coyote_m06_00800.mission: Look for RK Guys in Town
coyote_m06_00800.mission_info: We can't rely on Yagami-san alone. There must be something I can do to help, maybe in Kamurocho.

coyote_m06_01000.mission_info: I was hoping to talk to some RK members, but I don't know where to find them. Well, no worries. I know the owner of Tender, who's really well-connected. I'm sure he'd be willing to help.

coyote_m06_01400.mission: Lure RK Out Onto Senryo Avenue
coyote_m06_01400.mission_info: Time to walk down Senryo Avenue. If any RK guys approach us, we'll just reel them in. Then I can ask them about Shinya Kawai and see what they've found out so far.

coyote_m06_01540.mission_info: Sawa-sensei can't talk right now because she's in a staff meeting. Guess I'm on standby for a while... I heard Amasawa wanted to discuss something, so I might as well do that to kill some time.

coyote_m06_01580.mission_info: The staff meeting has gotta be over by now. I'll check the faculty room to see if Sawa-sensei's in there.

coyote_m06_01700.mission: Talk to Someone Who Might Know Sawa's Home Address
coyote_m06_01700.mission_info: There was a break-in at Sawa-sensei's apartment? Weird timing... I don't think I should let this go. Maybe someone who works at the school in a decently high position could tell me her address...

coyote_m06_01800.mission_info: Sawa-sensei's apartment is on Daikokuten Avenue, which should be near Hamakita Park. She's not picking up her phone, so I wanna check on her.

coyote_btl07_010.mission_info: Damn, Kuwana and Akutsu!? Why's everyone here at Sawa-sensei's apartment? Apparently, Kuwana's the one that RK's after. They're ready to take us down by any means, so I guess there's no choice but to fight!

coyote_btl07_020.mission_info: Fortunately, Sawa-sensei's okay—turns out Kuwana's the one RK's after. For now, gotta make sure he doesn't get caught. But he and Sawa-sensei better talk after all this!

coyote_m07_00300.mission_info: Is Kuwana all right? He took off down the building with Akutsu and his goons in pursuit. Better hurry and see if he needs a hand!

coyote_btl07_030.mission_info: Akutsu seems to be targeting Kuwana, who came to see Sawa-sensei. The hell's going on here? I need to find out who Kuwana really is. But first, we beat down Akutsu and his men!

coyote_btl07_040.mission_info: That was too close... Nearly got chopped to pieces. I owe Kaito-san and Sugiura big time. And as for Akutsu, I owe him a little something, too—an ass-kicking!

coyote_m07_00700.mission_info: Man, I let both Kuwana and Akutsu run off. Not good. But I bet Sawa-sensei knows something. At the very least, I can find out how she and Kuwana are connected. Let's head to her room.

coyote_m08_00500.mission_info: I've been summoned to the chairman's office. How do I go in there and face him now that Sawa-sensei's— One step at a time, Yagami. Just show up first.

coyote_m08_00800.mission_info: Just like the chairman, I'm worried about Class 2-2... Sawa-sensei's class. I should see how they're holding up before I leave campus.

coyote_m08_00900.mission_info: Considering Sawa-sensei just passed away, a sad gloom has fallen over the entire campus. Let's leave for now.

coyote_m08_01000.mission_info: Let's head back to Tsukumo's office for now and discuss our next moves.

coyote_m08_01100.mission_info: Better talk to Tsukumo so we can talk about our next moves with everyone.

coyote_m08_01400.mission_info: Kuwana's the Ijincho handyman, so his place has got to be in Ijincho. He apparently lives in some kinda prefab shack off West Central Street. Right now, this is top priority.

coyote_btl08_010.mission_info: Just a bunch of RK small fries, but I'll make them tell me where to find Akutsu and Soma!

coyote_m08_02000.mission_info: Kuwana's distant relative and ex-yakuza owns Siren. If I can talk to him, I might just get a lead on Kuwana's location. The bar's in Chinatown. Gotta get there before RK does.

coyote_btl08_020.mission_info: Soma! He's the one who killed Sawa-sensei, and now he's stabbed Kaito-san! This is the one bastard I'll never forgive!

coyote_m09_00300.mission_info: The owner of Siren says he's got something to tell me. I need to get over to Survive in the entertainment district, quick.

coyote_m09_00450.mission: Talk to the Owner of Siren
coyote_m09_00450.mission_info: If I talk to the owner of Siren, I might be able to get a lead on Kuwana's whereabouts... If I don't, then I'm out of options. Can't miss my chance.

coyote_m09_00600.mission: Take the USB Drive to Tsukumo
coyote_m09_00600.mission_info: Siren's owner risked his neck to meet with me to get the USB from Kuwana's office. I want to see what's inside as soon as possible. I should hurry over to Yokohama 99 and have the tech wizard work his magic.

coyote_btl09_010.mission_info: The White Masks think I'm with RK? You've gotta be kidding me...!

coyote_m09_01250.mission_info: Things are getting messy... I'm worried about Kaito-san, but there's nothing I can do now. I need to get some rest.

coyote_m09_01500.mission_info: I'm sure Sugiura has a car ready for us over at Yokohama 99 by now. We're heading to Tokyo to meet with Yui Mamiya... and it's going differently this time.

coyote_btl09_020.mission_info: Mamiya's backup turned out to be the masked men from Ijincho!? They're the ones who hired the White Masks and broke Tsukumo's pinky! Big mistake, folks...

coyote_m09_02000.mission_info: Yui Mamiya's finally starting to reveal her true colors—and I'm more certain than ever that she's involved with Kuwana. Let's hear what she has to say.

coyote_m09_02200.mission: Head to the Yagami Detective Agency
coyote_m09_02200.mission_info: I haven't seen Kuwana since that time at Sawa-sensei's apartment... I've got plenty of questions for him, and he's not getting away without some answers!

coyote_btl09_030.mission_info: I hadn't realized how desperate these masked men were... Let's get this over with so I can get back to tracking down Kuwana!

coyote_m10_00300.mission_info: Guess I'll take a break until Saori-san and Hoshino arrive. I'd like to know what RK's up to, so I'll head into Kamurocho for a bit.

coyote_m10_00400.mission_info: Saori-san and Hoshino have arrived, so let's head back to Charles. Yui Mamiya's going to tell me everything this time.

coyote_m10_00500.mission_info: This time, I'm getting every last detail out of Yui Mamiya. She needs to fill in every last hole in this story.

coyote_m10_00750.mission: Hit the Couch at Yagami Detective Agency
coyote_m10_00750.mission_info: We got everything we need. Tomorrow's our interview with Ehara. Time to call it a day and rest up at Yagami Detective Agency.

coyote_m10_00850.mission: Take a Taxi to the Detention Center
coyote_m10_00850.mission_info: Time for us to interview Ehara. Better take a cab to Tokyo Detention Center. We can pick up Saori-san on the way.

coyote_m10_01100.mission_info: From this point on, we're working on Ehara's appeal. I'll have to meet with Genda-sensei about what to do next, too. Everyone should be waiting for me at Genda Law Office.

coyote_m10_01300.mission_info: I've done everything I can in Kamurocho. Now it's time to head back to Yokohama 99 and sort things out with Tsukumo.

coyote_m10_01400.mission_info: I get how Kuwana and Ehara are connected, but where does RK come into all this? Why did Sawa-sensei have to die? I just want to grab them by the throat and make them tell me... Let's take a look around Ijincho for them.

coyote_m10_01500.mission_info: Saori-san dropped a bombshell. Reiko Kusumoto—the Vice Minister of the Ministry of Health—is also the mother of a bullying victim. There's a good chance Kuwana was in contact with her, just like he was with Ehara. Better head back to Yokohama 99 and gather some info.

coyote_m10_01700.mission: Meet with Detective Watanabe in Chinatown
coyote_m10_01700.mission_info: Seems like Detective Watanabe can't continue the investigation due to pressure from his superiors. I'll see what I can gather from him. He should still be somewhere in Chinatown.

coyote_btl10_010.mission_info: Nabe-san's not a bad guy, but the bigwigs in the police force are definitely acting shady. You're gonna need to calm down, Nabe-san!

coyote_m10_01900.mission_info: Kuwana hasn't bailed out of Ijincho yet? In any case, sounds like I better head for Geomijul right away. If the cops get Kuwana before I get there, he'll wind up in an "accident"!

coyote_btl10_020.mission_info: What's RK planning to do once they capture Kuwana? I'd be lucky if these idiots knew a damn thing, but either way, I'm gonna get them talking!

coyote_m10_02500.mission: Head to the Yokohama Liumang's Hideout
coyote_m10_02500.mission_info: Kuwana's in Yokohama Liumang territory. So he's rolling with them now? Better get over there fast.

coyote_btl10_030.mission_info: Kuwana tried to defend Reiko Kusumoto, who has blood on her hands. But that means the reason Sawa-sensei was killed—and the truth—will all get buried and forgotten. And I can't let that happen. She's not alive to defend herself anymore, so we're the only ones who can now!

coyote_m10_02900.mission_info: We're going to set a trap to find out for sure if Public Security really is our enemy. Let's head to Yokohama 99. Tsukumo should already have the burner phones ready to go.

coyote_m10_03000.mission: Head to the Building Construction Site
coyote_m10_03000.mission_info: The construction site near Seiryo High... No one'll get hurt on the off chance Public Security is sent there. And it's the perfect spot to spring our trap. Let's check it out.

coyote_btl10_040.mission_info: Looks like these guys are small time RK. Public Security traced the call and sent them here. This proves Public Security was backing RK all along... and that they're also responsible for Sawa-sensei's death!

coyote_m11_00150.mission: Take a Taxi to Touto University Hospital
coyote_m11_00150.mission_info: I need to take a taxi to Touto University Hospital and have Reiko Kusumoto explain everything to me directly. If she turns herself in and exposes Public Security's secrets, they can't operate under the radar anymore.

coyote_m11_00400.mission_info: Just in case, I should let Kuwana know I talked to Reiko Kusumoto. He's still with Tesso at the Yokohama Liumang's hideout.

coyote_m11_00450.mission_info: I should call it a day. Time to head back to Yokohama 99 and rest up for tomorrow.

coyote_m11_00550.mission: Take a Taxi to the Courthouse
coyote_m11_00550.mission_info: A preliminary discussion regarding Ehara's appeal at the courthouse, huh. Is the court planning to deny the appeal? If that's the case, we'll just have to convince them otherwise. Gotta grab a taxi to the courthouse.

coyote_m11_00800.mission_info: Bando from Public Security... I wonder if our enemy is feeling cornered and that's why he exposed his face to me? In any case, I need to plan my next move. Should I meet up with Saori-san and the others...?

coyote_m11_00950.mission_info: Apparently, Hoshino-kun heard some gossip about RK.

coyote_m11_01200.mission_info: I've got some time until Saori-san's ready. I might as well head into town and run some errands, and then wait for her at the beauty salon.

coyote_m11_01500.mission_info: I should head out to Queen Rouge. I can do this... I've gone undercover there before.

coyote_btl11_010.mission_info: I finally found you, Akutsu...! If there's anyone in RK who'd know where Soma is, it's you. Get ready to spill the beans!

coyote_m12_00300.mission: Walk Saori Back to the Office
coyote_m12_00300.mission_info: I should escort Saori-san back to Genda Law. Saori-san's one tough cookie, but seeing someone get shot right in front of her... That'd affect nearly anyone.

coyote_m12_00400.mission: Hit the Couch at Yagami Detective Agency
coyote_m12_00400.mission_info: I guess that's it for tonight. Let's head back to the office and get some rest.

coyote_m12_00600.mission_info: Higashi apparently knows about Soma's Tojo Clan days. I need to learn as much about Soma as possible if I'm going to figure out his motive...

coyote_m12_00900.mission_info: Time to head over to Earth Angel. The former head of Tojo Clan's Nikkyo Consortium, Irie-san, should be there...

coyote_m12_01100.mission_info: RK's going to raid the tatami room, and there's a chance Soma will be there too. Time to move!

coyote_btl12_020.mission_info: This is a pretty large-scale operation... I heard all the ex-Tojo members in RK are in on it. Maybe Soma's here too!

coyote_btl12_030.mission_info: Damn, what was even the point of coming here, then...? I guess we'll just say we came to save Kosuke-kun, like Kaito-san said!

coyote_m12_01550.mission: Hit the Couch at Yagami Detective Agency
coyote_m12_01550.mission_info: I should head back to the office and get some rest. We'll head to Ijincho again tomorrow to find Kuwana.

coyote_m12_01650.mission_info: Time to meet with Tsukumo and discuss our next steps. But Ijincho is chock-full of RK right now...

coyote_m12_01800.mission_info: I should scope out what's going on in Ijincho. Hopefully I can somehow find a lead on either Kuwana or Soma.

coyote_m12_01900.mission: Head to the Yokohama Liumang hideout
coyote_m12_01900.mission_info: I'll go to the area controlled by the Yokohama Liumang—I doubt RK can keep a bead on me in there! Just gotta pull a solid vanishing act, and then I can go see Kuwana. I'll check in on Tesso too, since I heard the Liumang was attacked recently. He's my Ijincho brother, after all.

coyote_m12_02000.mission_info: Exactly what you would expect of a notorious gang's hideout. They even have a secret tunnel! Tesso's willing to show me the way through, so I'll follow him.

coyote_m12_02300.mission: Head to the Front of Sawa's Apartment Building
coyote_m12_02300.mission_info: On to Sawa-sensei's apartment! Kuwana said I'll get picked up there. I think he's feeling the walls close in on him.

coyote_btl12_040.mission_info: The fact that Soma and RK showed up means that there was a betrayal by Reiko Kusumoto. But I thought Kuwana was going to protect her forever... Well, anyhow, we've gotta make it through this!

coyote_m13_00300.mission_info: Time to form our plan of attack. I'll go hash it out with everyone at Yokohama 99.

coyote_m13_00500.mission_info: Time to prep for Ehara's appeal in Kamurocho. I can't let Saori-san do this alone. Let's head to Genda Law Office.

coyote_m13_00600.mission: Kill Some Time Until Saori's Ready to Go
coyote_m13_00600.mission_info: Will we really learn anything new by interviewing Ehara again? Guess it doesn't hurt to try. I'll head into town until Saori-san's ready to go.

coyote_m13_00670.mission: Take a Taxi to the Detention Center
coyote_m13_00670.mission_info: Time for us to interview Ehara. Better take a cab to Tokyo Detention Center. We can pick up Saori-san on the way.

coyote_m13_00850.mission: Make Preparations and Head to Ijincho
coyote_m13_00850.mission_info: Kaito-san and the others are looking for Kuwana in Ijincho. Do I have anything left to do before I go back?

coyote_m13_01000.mission: Head to the Yokohama Liumang's Hideout
coyote_m13_01000.mission_info: Kaito-san's at the Yokohama Liumang's place. Might be a good idea to go meet up there.

coyote_m13_01300.mission_info: No luck finding Kuwana or Soma. So I guess that means we're done in Ijincho, then? Once I'm ready, I'll head over to Yokohama 99.

coyote_m13_01550.mission_info: I need to go to where Mikoshiba's body was found. Koda-san and possibly Akane are being held hostage there!

coyote_btl13_010.mission_info: I'm not holding back against these scumbags—not after the things they've done!

coyote_m13_01650.mission_info: It's almost time for Ehara's appeal. Our plan is to reject the sexual battery charge and assert Ehara's innocence on the grounds that he was murdering Mikoshiba as the groping took place. Okay, let's take a taxi to the courthouse.

coyote_m13_02000.mission_info: We have to get to the warehouse company where Kuwana's at, and fast. I just need to take Isezaki Road and have Sugiura pick me up on Tsurukame Highway.

coyote_btl13_020.mission_info: RK's always got numbers, I'll give 'em that. We need to get to Kuwana fast. This is not the time to be screwing around with them!

coyote_btl13_030.mission_info: Both Kuwana and Soma should be here at this warehouse. Don't overthink things now. Just keep charging forward!

coyote_btl13_040.mission_info: Both Kuwana and Soma should be here at this warehouse. Don't overthink things now. Just keep charging forward!

coyote_btl13_050.mission_info: So Kuwana was using himself and Kawai's body as bait to lure Soma out. Either way, we better hurry. Kuwana's in the far back of the underground warehouse!

coyote_btl13_060.mission_info: This is it. Time to take down Soma and everybody in RK with him. Thankfully, I've got my whole gang backing me up. And that's why we're not gonna lose!

coyote_btl13_070.mission_info: Am I the one who's wrong? Or is Kuwana? In any case, I can't turn my back on this now or else Sawa-sensei's sacrifice would've been for nothing. And I won't let that happen, Kuwana!

coyote_g09_030.mission_info: I can't let Kuwana escape. I'm done letting him have his way... Especially since I know what it is! I'm gonna catch him no matter what!

coyote_side_m05_0020.mission_info: Time to head over to M Side Cafe and find Ryan.

coyote_side_g05_0010.mission_info: I need to find Ryan. He seems to be hiding somewhere...

coyote_side_m05_0040.mission: Head to the Dojo on Senryo Avenue
coyote_side_m05_0040.mission_info: Let's see if I can infiltrate a ninja school.

coyote_side_m05_0045.mission: Follow the Dojo's Mandatory Dress Code
coyote_side_m05_0045.mission_info: I gotta follow the dress code to enter the dojo... Seriously though?

coyote_side_g05_0020.mission_info: Just gotta catch Kalashnikov. No problem.

coyote_side_btl05_0010.mission_info: Time to take this guy down!

coyote_btl07_025_010.mission_info: Is Kuwana all right? He took off down the building with Akutsu and his goons in pursuit. Better hurry and see if he needs a hand!

coyote_btl07_025_020.mission_info: Is Kuwana all right? He took off down the building with Akutsu and his goons in pursuit. Better hurry and see if he needs a hand!

coyote_side_m06_0020.mission: Look Myself Up on the Buzz Researcher
coyote_side_m06_0020.mission_info: Sounds like I've got some bad rumors spreading through town... Let's see what the Buzz Researcher can pull up for me.

coyote_side_m06_0030.mission: Conduct Interviews in the Champion District
coyote_side_m06_0030.mission_info: Apparently, I've been sighted in the Champion District real recently. I should go there and ask around.

coyote_side_m06_0050.mission: Slip past the Murderous Old Men
coyote_side_m06_0050.mission_info: Just what I needed, armed triplets who want my head on a platter! I can't fight back against these guys, but I really need to get out of here...

coyote_side_m06_0070.mission_info: Good thing those grandpas didn't slice me up... I need to find out what's going on, and fast. Tender might be the best place to start asking around.

coyote_side_m06_0080.mission_info: The police were interviewing Masuda...? I hope he knows what's happening here.

coyote_side_g06_0010.mission_info: Someone was using my office without my permission. I should try to find some evidence the culprit left behind—it could give me a lead.

coyote_side_m06_0110.mission: Use the Scent to Go After the Culprit
coyote_side_m06_0110.mission_info: Woof, this chili shrimp reeks... It's still hot too, so whoever was eating it couldn't have gotten far. This scent should be the key to going after the culprit.

coyote_side_btl06_0010.mission_info: Not cool, Sakakiba. I'm gonna teach you a lesson!

coyote_side_m08_0030.mission_info: Sounds like some kind of robbery's going on in Alps... Something tells me this isn't a movie shoot. I ought to check it out. Maybe I should make an Observation of the entrance of the place.

coyote_side_g08_0010.mission: Head to the Back of Café Alps
coyote_side_g08_0010.mission_info: The sign said there was a movie shoot taking place, but it also said "SOS"... Something tells me I should look into this a bit more.

coyote_side_m08_0060.mission: Find a Way to Approach the Robber
coyote_side_m08_0060.mission_info: Boy, do I hate being right... I have to find a way to close in on the robber safely. Let's see if there's anything in this alley I could use...

coyote_side_g08_0020.mission_info: Okay. Time to get closer to the robber, as close as possible!

coyote_side_btl08_0010.mission_info: The robber caught me before I could get my hands on him. No choice now but to stop him by force.

coyote_side_g08_0030.mission_info: His hostage was in cahoots with him! I can't let him get away like that.

coyote_side_m009_020.mission_info: Apparently there's been some sort of "mascot outbreak" at Children's Park... Gotta say, that phrase at least has me curious.

coyote_side_m009_030.mission: Find the Source of the Voice
coyote_side_m009_030.mission_info: I think I heard a weak voice come from one of the Kamulop costumes. I should use the noise amp to see if I'm right.

coyote_side_m009_040.mission: Bring the Parched Girl Some Water
coyote_side_m009_040.mission_info: Poor girl nearly had a heat stroke in one of the Kamulops. I better bring her something to drink—quick.

coyote_side_m009_070.mission_info: Well, I don't exactly know what I'm supposed to be doing... I guess I help people in trouble out fairly often as it is—maybe I'll stick to that for now.

coyote_side_m10_0020.mission: Look for the Senryo Avenue Stalker
coyote_side_m10_0020.mission_info: There's a rumor on Chatter about a stalker who's on the loose, day and night, around Senryo Avenue. I should go there and take a look.

coyote_side_m10_0030.mission_info: An invisible burglar? I should hear what Kiba-san has to say.

coyote_side_m10_0040.mission_info: I'm going to investigate Kiba-san's office building, and then I'll report what I find.

coyote_side_g10_0010.mission_info: I should leave no stone unturned in Sakurazaka-san's office and use my power of observation if I want to find out who the invisible burglar is. Might even be the time to bust out a gadget.

coyote_side_m17_0020.mission_info: I agreed to meet up with Minato-chan to return her notebook. I should get over there and wait for her.

coyote_side_m93_0020.mission: Talk to Tsukino During the Day or Evening
coyote_side_m93_0020.mission_info: I'm going to help Tsukino-chan get some pictures for the school website. I should talk to her once I'm ready. Probably best around the day or in the evening when the students are still around.

coyote_side_m93_0025.mission_info: I should head to the Seiryo High gymnasium with Tsukino-chan so we can photograph the dodgeball club.

coyote_side_m93_0040.mission_info: I need a picture of Tsuruno-kun dodging the ball in a cool way. I should try to get his face in frame, as well as the person throwing the ball.

coyote_side_m93_0055.mission_info: Tsukino-chan seems down. Hopefully I can help take her mind off things.

coyote_side_m94_0020.mission: Talk to Tsukino During the Day or Evening
coyote_side_m94_0020.mission_info: I'll be helping Tsukino-chan some more today. I should talk to her once I'm ready. Probably best around the day or in the evening when the students are still around.

coyote_side_m94_0025.mission_info: This time I'm taking pictures of the dance club for Tsukino-chan. Nishizono and the others ought to be willing to help out.

coyote_side_m94_0040.mission_info: Hoo boy... So, big smiles, Maria's right side at a 45-degree angle, Nishizono center frame, and Takanashi wants it to be "sexy"? This is getting absurd...

coyote_side_m94_0045.mission_info: Tsukino-chan seems pretty nervous to square off with Fujita-sensei. I should check this out, maybe lend some support.

coyote_side_m96_0012.mission_info: I'm not here for an investigation today, so I should just cut loose and have fun.

coyote_side_m96_0015.mission_info: Emily-chan just woke up and wants some coffee to get her going. Time to take her to a café.

coyote_side_m97_0030.mission: Meet Emily in Front of the Station
coyote_side_m97_0030.mission_info: I invited Emily-chan out to escort her. We're meeting in front of the station.

coyote_side_m97_0035.mission: Take Emily Out for Chinese Food
coyote_side_m97_0035.mission_info: I'm escorting Emily-chan today. We're going to a Chinese restaurant.

coyote_side_m97_0075.mission_info: Time to head to Girl's Bite with Emily-chan.

coyote_side_m100_0020.mission_info: The cat Hakase-san's taking care of is at school. This could be my chance to build a connection with it.

coyote_side_m100_0050.mission: Go to the Nurse's Office at Night
coyote_side_m100_0050.mission_info: Hasegawa-sensei had something come up, so instead of going out with her, Hakase-san is getting a drink with me. I should pick her up at the nurse's office tonight.

coyote_side_m100_0055.mission_info: Gotta head to the restaurant while I walk and talk with Hakase-san.

coyote_side_btl100_0010.mission_info: He's a hopeless case, a man who can only think about himself. But I won't let him get away with this.

coyote_side_m99_0055.mission_info: I decided to walk Hakase-san most of her way home. Maybe we can have some nice conversation, too.

coyote_side_btl99_0010.mission_info: This city isn't so peaceful, I guess. I should take care of this and walk Hakase-san back to her place.

coyote_side_m17_0030.mission_info: We agreed to head over to Alps... though it feels more like I'm talking to Kamulop than Minato-chan.

coyote_side_m18_0020.mission_info: Minato-chan and I are going to compete in the manzai contest together... I should find her at the Tenkaichi Street entrance at night.

coyote_side_m18_0030.mission_info: I need to get to the manzai contest in Theater Square with Minato-chan, ASAP.

coyote_side_m19_0025.mission_info: When I'm ready to hear Minato-chan out, I should head over to Children's Park at night.

coyote_side_m63_0015.mission: Go to the MRC in the Evening
coyote_side_m63_0015.mission_info: Amasawa needs my help with something. She wants me to stop by in the evening.

coyote_side_m63_0030.mission_info: I'm meeting Amasawa at a café called Plage about this issue one of her classmates is having.

coyote_side_m63_0060.mission_info: Shimada-kun's father apparently purchased the unlucky cat at the Ebisu Pawn in Ijincho. I should go there first.

coyote_side_g63_0010.mission_info: I have a feeling that fire was arson-related... I'll check the area with Observation.

coyote_side_m63_0100.mission_info: We've decided to lure out the culprit. Time to hit the local batting center.

coyote_side_m63_0130.mission_info: Let's just slip out this way, real smooth-like...

coyote_side_m63_0140.mission: Sneak Up on the Suspicious Man
coyote_side_m63_0140.mission_info: That guy's eyeing the unlucky cat pretty hard... Let's see what he has to say. Carefully.

coyote_side_btl63_0010.mission_info: Why's this guy want the statue so badly? Maybe he knows the truth about Kitan Amasawa's death...

coyote_side_g63_0020.mission_info: I need to uncover the secrets of this cat statue!

coyote_side_m65_0015.mission_info: I'm worried about that lady who seemed scared for her life... Maybe I should go talk to her.

coyote_side_m65_0030.mission_info: A woman named Kyoko Hakase was afraid someone was watching her. She said she'd call me if she felt that way again. I need to do something before this gets out of hand, but I still need to wait for her call.

coyote_side_g65_0010.mission: Find the Person Gazing at Hakase
coyote_side_g65_0010.mission_info: Hakase-san says she feels a suspicious gaze on her. Better keep an eye out for whoever's looking at her.

coyote_side_btl69_0010.mission_info: Yeah, this guy really needs to be stopped, and fast.

coyote_side_m69_0030.mission_info: Kodama-san's recruited me to find the kappa statues he placed all over town. Hope I'm able to help...

coyote_side_g69_0010.mission_info: I have no idea why that guy's running around with a kappa statue, but I need to get it from him!

coyote_side_m071_010.mission: Meet the Client at Wette Kitchen
coyote_side_m071_010.mission_info: I should get over to the Wette Kitchen in Ijincho to meet with my client.

coyote_side_g071_010.mission_info: I need to follow Toru-kun as he performs his first errand. Gotta be extra-careful that I'm not spotted...

coyote_side_m72_0020.mission_info: This kinda just sounds like another scary story, but based on some of these Chatter posts, I should at least look into it the next time I'm at Seiryo at night.

coyote_side_m72_0030.mission_info: If I'm already here, I may as well poke around and see if I can find that body model.

coyote_side_m72_0040.mission_info: Okay, I think I just saw something running... Toward the second year classrooms? I have to check, just to be sure.

coyote_side_g72_0010.mission_info: I think it went into one of these classrooms... Maybe the noise amp will pick it up?

coyote_side_g72_0020.mission_info: I can't believe it really moves...! Now I have to catch it!

coyote_side_m72_0080.mission_info: Well, that wasn't so much an animated body model as a student with misdirected efforts... I should chat with him the next time I see him.

coyote_side_m69_0015.mission_info: Clearly I got here late, but if this guy's running wild swinging around a statue, someone needs to intervene. Let's find out what's going on.

coyote_side_m69_0025.mission_info: Kodama-san's needs help finding his kappa statues... He seems pretty troubled over it, so I should give him a hand when I can.

coyote_side_m071_015.mission_info: I should speak with Manaka-san when I'm ready to watch over his son while he performs his first errand.

coyote_drama_m34_210.mission_info: Looks like the next opponent in my counter-Kenya training is the sixth-ranked bantamweight in the OBPF, Yum. When I'm ready, I should talk to Todoroki.

coyote_drama_m34_220.mission_info: Apparently, Amasawa has an idea about the Payback Boxer's next target. Let's head to the MRC club room and see what's up.

coyote_drama_m34_300.mission_info: Todoroki's putting together a special counter-Kenya training program for me. I should give it my best so I can win against Oshikiri.

coyote_drama_m34_305.mission: Defeat Heavyweight Sakuma in a Match
coyote_drama_m34_305.mission_info: Looks like Sakuma's going to be even more of a powerhouse this time... I'll go see Todoroki when I'm ready for the match.

coyote_drama_m34_400.mission_info: Todoroki's putting together a special counter-Kenya training program for me. I should give it my best so I can win against Oshikiri.

coyote_drama_m34_410.mission_info: Todoroki's willing to get in the ring with me for Oshikiri's sake. Sure hope this doesn't go poorly... The guy was an OPBF champion.

coyote_drama_m34_420.mission_info: Now that I've beaten Todoroki in a match, he says I'm finally ready to take on Oshikiri for real. He'll let me know when he's ready for us to go.

coyote_drama_m34_430.mission: Head to the MRC Club Room
coyote_drama_m34_430.mission_info: Today's the day we lure out the Payback Boxer. Better go meet up with Amasawa.

coyote_drama_m34_435.mission: Kick Off the Plan with Amasawa
coyote_drama_m34_435.mission_info: I should speak with Amasawa once I'm ready to move out and trap the Payback Boxer.

coyote_drama_m34_440.mission_info: If Oshikiri really is the Payback Boxer, spotting me would blow the whole operation. I should get incognito so I can tail this guy properly.

coyote_drama_m34_500.mission_info: You and me, Oshikiri... This time, it's going to go a lot differently.

coyote_ drama_btl34_010.mission_info: Honda brought in the Neo Keihin Gang to raid Torodoki's gym. Time to get these guys outta here!

coyote_ drama_btl34_020.mission_info: Fudo Oshikiri's here! Time to take back Kenya's future—for good!

coyote_drama_m21_020.mission_info: At Amasawa's request, I'm infiltrating the Robotics Club. They don't trust adults, so Amasawa was worried how they'd receive me.

coyote_drama_m21_030.mission: Talk to the Robotics Club Members
coyote_drama_m21_030.mission_info: Well, they don't seem to be in a welcoming mood. Guess I'll talk to everybody one by one to introduce myself.

coyote_drama_m21_080.mission: Report on the Robotics Club to Amasawa
coyote_drama_m21_080.mission_info: Amasawa was worried the Robotics Club would reject me, so I should head back to the MRC and report that they've accepted me.

coyote_drama_m21_090.mission_info: Too bad Itokura doesn't want to help with the investigation. Guess I'll have to proceed with the Robotics Club on my own for the time being. Our goal: get through the preliminaries.

coyote_drama_m21_190.mission: Ask for Itokura's Assistance at the MRC
coyote_drama_m21_190.mission_info: Sakura-kun from the Robotics Club is having trouble with programming. Would Itokura be willing to help out? Guess I'll go ask her again.

coyote_drama_m21_210.mission_info: Itokura went up to the roof. She's finally made her way back to school, but at this rate, she'll stop coming again. Better hurry.

coyote_drama_m21_230.mission_info: Itokura's decided to come help out the Robotics Club. I need to continue the investigation. The team's aiming to get past the preliminaries in the robot competition.

coyote_drama_m21_250.mission: Find Sakura and Itokura at the Cafeteria
coyote_drama_m21_250.mission_info: Gotta meet up with Sakura-kun and Itokura at the cafeteria and ask Sakura-kun everything I can about the Robotics Club. Hopefully I can get some sort of lead on the thief-bot.

coyote_drama_m21_260.mission_info: To investigate the thieving robot incidents, I need to keep going undercover in the Robotics Club. Gotta help them get through the preliminaries.

coyote_drama_m21_270.mission: Head to the RE Robot Rally Preliminaries
coyote_drama_m21_270.mission_info: It's finally time for the RE Robo Rally preliminaries. We make it through here, and we're in the main tournament. Let's do this!

coyote_drama_m22_010.mission_info: Well, we made it through the preliminaries somehow. Next up is round one of the main tournament. I need to guide the Robotics Club to victory as I investigate further.

coyote_drama_m22_060.mission: Find Sakura and the Others at the Cafeteria
coyote_drama_m22_060.mission_info: The bolts used in the thief-bot are the same custom-made ones used by the Robotics Club. Better ask Sakura-kun about this.

coyote_drama_m22_070.mission_info: I have to guide the team past the first round of the RE Robo Rally as I continue my investigation of the thief-bot.

coyote_drama_m23_010.mission_info: We made it through the first round of the competition. Can't lose my focus on the ever-critical thieving robot incident.

coyote_drama_m23_020.mission: Talk to Amasawa at the MRC
coyote_drama_m23_020.mission_info: Amasawa called me over, probably so we can share info regarding the Robotics Club investigation. Better head over to the MRC later.

coyote_drama_m23_030.mission_info: I learned some disquieting info about Okitegawa. I should get back to the Robotics Club and continue the investigation.

coyote_drama_m23_160.mission: Report to the Robotics Club on Kurumazaki-kun
coyote_drama_m23_160.mission_info: Think I should head back to the Robotics Club and report on Kurumazaki-kun.

coyote_drama_m23_170.mission_info: Kurumazaki-kun, Takamori, and even Itokura stormed out of the club room. I better talk to Itokura. Where could she have gone?

coyote_drama_m23_180.mission: Return to the Club Room and Follow Up
coyote_drama_m23_180.mission_info: The Robotics Club split up... Better go feel out the situation at the club room.

coyote_drama_m23_190.mission: Head to Round Two of the RE Robo Rally
coyote_drama_m23_190.mission_info: It's time for round two of the competition. We only have a handful of members, but we can't afford to lose.

coyote_drama_m24_010.mission_info: Things are getting rough in the Robotics Club, but I can't stop investigating the thief-bot incident.

coyote_drama_m24_050.mission_info: Kurumazaki-kun has decided to come back. Okitegawa went to convince the other members as well. I'll go check in on the Robotics Club later.

coyote_drama_m24_080.mission_info: The Robotics Club managed to make up and stay together, but the next practice match is just ahead. I should head to the club room to check how things are.

coyote_drama_m24_120.mission: Look in the Robotics Club Cabinet
coyote_drama_m24_120.mission_info: I was given the Robotics Club's cabinet key by Okitegawa as a symbol of trust. Time to take a look inside the cabinet with Amasawa.

coyote_drama_m24_130.mission: Meet Up with Kurumazaki at the Cafeteria
coyote_drama_m24_130.mission_info: The blueprints of the robot in the Robotics Club cabinet were created by Kurumazaki-kun, and it bears a striking resemblance to the thief-bot. Seems like I need to talk to him.

coyote_drama_m24_140.mission: Head to the Neo Keihin Gang Hideout
coyote_drama_m24_140.mission_info: I should head for the Neo Keihin Gang hideout Kurumazaki-kun told me about. The building's near the edge of town on East Tsurukame Highway.

coyote_drama_btl24_010.mission: Take Out the Neo Keihin Punks
coyote_drama_btl24_010.mission_info: These are the guys who were threatening Kurumazaki-kun. Time to teach them a lesson.

coyote_drama_m24_180.mission_info: I've got the thief-bot. Time to head back to the Robotics Club room.

coyote_drama_m24_200.mission_info: The thieving robot incident was resolved, but my duties as the club's counselor haven't ended. Gotta get ready for the finals.

coyote_drama_m24_240.mission: Compete in the RE Robo Rally Finals
coyote_drama_m24_240.mission_info: The final match is here. Time to give it everything we've got and take home the victory!

coyote_drama_m24_270.mission: Meet Up with Tsukumo at the MRC
coyote_drama_m24_270.mission_info: Tsukumo's done analyzing the laptop from the Neo Keihin Gang hideout. He's headed to the MRC club room. Time to go hear the results with Amasawa.

coyote_drama_m91_010.mission_info: Rumor's been getting around about someone called the Professor who's helping kids commit crimes. Sounds like a tall tale to me, but as the MRC advisor, I should look into it.

coyote_drama_m91_020.mission_info: Time to look back on all the incidents I've investigated for Amasawa... Hopefully we find a lead on the Professor. I'll catch up with Amasawa at noon.

coyote_drama_m91_030.mission_info: Apparently, Kento-kun's in some trouble. I should get over to the Poppo in front of Jinnai Station.

coyote_drama_m91_045.mission_info: Kento-kun's been abducted! The only clues we've got are his bag and his wallet. I have to figure out where he is somehow...

coyote_drama_btl91_0100.mission_info: Let's shut these jerks up and get Kento-kun outta here.

coyote_drama_m91_110.mission_info: I really hope we're getting this wrong, but...

coyote_drama_m91_160.mission: Head to the Yamakawa Towels Building
coyote_drama_m91_160.mission_info: I'm pretty sure the Neo Keihin Gang's robot workshop was in the building on East Tsurukame Highway with the little white sign...

coyote_drama_btl91_0200.mission_info: Must be real important members, hanging around an abandoned building... Let's just get this over with.

coyote_drama_m91_190.mission_info: Nishizono and Takanashi found the car Itokura got in. I should meet them right away!

coyote_drama_m91_200.mission: Scale the Neo Keihin Gang Building
coyote_drama_m91_200.mission_info: The front's too well-guarded—I should climb up to the third floor and sneak in that way.

coyote_drama_btl91_0300.mission_info: We've got plenty of history together... Now, I'm bringing it to a close.

coyote_side_m73_0015.mission: Look Up UFOs on the Buzz Researcher
coyote_side_m73_0015.mission_info: Let's see what the Buzz Researcher finds on Chatter about UFOs in Ijincho.

coyote_side_m73_0020.mission: Search for UFOs at Night in the Bar District
coyote_side_m73_0020.mission_info: The UFO's been spotted at night in the Bar District. I'll head over then and see what I can observe.

coyote_side_m73_0030.mission_info: There's a rumor someone was abducted and taken away on a UFO. I should check for stories about that on the Buzz Researcher!

coyote_side_m73_0035.mission_info: Yabuki's gone bonkers over getting abducted. It's getting pretty bad... Maybe I should speak with him.

coyote_side_m73_0040.mission: Talk to Yabuki at Wette Kitchen
coyote_side_m73_0040.mission_info: Yabuki has something to discuss with me. I should go hear him out.

coyote_side_m73_0050.mission: Find a UFO and Take a Picture
coyote_side_m73_0050.mission_info: I should look up eyewitness reports on the Buzz Researcher to narrow down locations where I might be able to observe the UFO.

coyote_side_g73_0005.mission: Take a Picture of the UFO
coyote_side_g73_0005.mission_info: Found one! Time for some photographic evidence!

coyote_side_m73_0060.mission: Find a UFO and Take a Picture
coyote_side_m73_0060.mission_info: I should look up eyewitness reports on the Buzz Researcher to narrow down locations where I might be able to get a picture.

coyote_side_m73_0070.mission: Find the UFO at Seiryo High
coyote_side_m73_0070.mission_info: People are saying there's a UFO at Seiryo High... They're even saying it parks there.

coyote_side_m73_0075.mission: Ask the Students about the UFO
coyote_side_m73_0075.mission_info: These kids in the courtyard might know something about the UFO. I should go ask them.

coyote_side_g73_0008.mission: Take a Picture of the UFO
coyote_side_g73_0008.mission_info: It really came! Better get a picture!

coyote_side_g73_0010.mission_info: Wait, am I really about to catch a UFO!?

coyote_side_m88_0015.mission: Look Up Wiretapping on the Buzz Researcher
coyote_side_m88_0015.mission_info: These wiretapping problems seem to come from one corrupt detective who's been a real hot topic online. Let's see what the Buzz Researcher has to say.

coyote_side_m88_0020.mission_info: Seems like there's been a case of wiretapping near the district courthouse. Maybe I should check it out.

coyote_side_m88_0030.mission: Search for the Bug in the Parking Lot
coyote_side_m88_0030.mission_info: The courthouse parking lot seems to be giving off a signal... Tsukumo's detector ought to come in handy here.

coyote_side_m101_0030.mission: Meet Hakase at The Harbor Light
coyote_side_m101_0030.mission_info: Hakase-san wants to tell me something. We're planning to have drinks at The Harbor Light, which is good... Now I just need to muster the courage to go.

coyote_side_g103_0010.mission_info: If I'm supposed to be imitating this squirrel, then maybe I should listen for a sound. And I have just the gadget to help me.

coyote_side_m104_0013.mission_info: Futaba-chan found a squirrel picture. I should ask her to take me to it whenever I'm free.

coyote_side_m104_0015.mission_info: Time to look for that squirrel picture with Futaba-chan.

coyote_side_g104_0010.mission: Think About What's in the Picture
coyote_side_g104_0010.mission_info: If I want to do what's in this squirrel picture... Well at this point, I think I know how.

coyote_side_m106_0040.mission: Talk to Haruko at the Girls' Bar
coyote_side_m106_0040.mission_info: Haruko-chan is troubled by her relationship with her dad. If I keep coming by, she'll probably open up more about the situation.

coyote_side_m107_0030.mission: Talk to Miu at the Girls' Bar
coyote_side_m107_0030.mission_info: Miu-chan's got a stalker, and that's got me worried. Maybe she'll tell me more about it if I get friendlier with her.

coyote_side_g107_0005.mission_info: It's highly likely one of Miu-chan's belongings is bugged. I should scan Miu-chan with the detector. Might spot some suspicious radio waves.

coyote_side_g107_0010.mission_info: Is that Miu-chan's stalker? Better catch them and start asking questions.

coyote_side_g108_0010.mission_info: Doesn't matter how young he is. Stealing is wrong. Gotta catch him.

coyote_side_m108_0050.mission: Talk to Ayaha at the Girls' Bar
coyote_side_m108_0050.mission_info: Ayaha-chan confessed she's an otaku. Think I'll pop into the girls' bar to see how things are after everything that happened.

coyote_side_m110_0020.mission: Look for Shinonome on Sakura River Street
coyote_side_m110_0020.mission_info: The client's target, Shinonome, was last seen around Sakura River Street. I should head over there and look for him.

coyote_side_btl110_0010.mission_info: Man, this guy really went off the deep end... I have to get him seeing straight again.

coyote_side_m112_0040.mission_info: Wonder what's up with him. Clearly he's leading me somewhere...

coyote_side_m113_0020.mission_info: Momoyama works at Rose Blossom on Ohama Street. I ought to speak with the manager about her bugged handbag.

coyote_side_m114_0020.mission_info: I'm picking up a signal from the stuffed animal inside that UFO Catcher. I should try winning it before someone else does.

coyote_side_btl114_0010.mission_info: So this guy's the toy-bugger... Let's get this over with.

coyote_side_m115_0020.mission: Track the Drone Signal to its Owner
coyote_side_m115_0020.mission_info: Whoever's using this drone to spy in hotels, I'm comin' for ya...

coyote_side_g115_0010.mission_info: That old perv's got quite the nimble feet. I'd better catch him before he gets away.

coyote_side_m116_0020.mission_info: A bug signal's coming from this wallet. I should find its owner and let him know... The cologne it reeks with ought to help me.

coyote_side_m117_0020.mission: Track the Signal Source in Seiryo High
coyote_side_m117_0020.mission_info: Oh, no. Seiryo High's giving off a bug signal. If I find out someone's creeping on these kids...

coyote_side_m117_0060.mission: Check Out the Signal in the MRC
coyote_side_m117_0060.mission_info: The signal's coming from the MRC. I know Amasawa's a bit mysterious, but I doubt she's actually emitting any electromagnetic waves. So what's the source of this?

coyote_side_m118_0020.mission: Find the Bug on the Woman
coyote_side_m118_0020.mission_info: Apparently this lady's been getting harassed by a stalker, and it seems that she's been bugged. I should lend her a hand.

coyote_side_g119_0010.mission_info: That man who collected the bugged ramen bowl... Could he be the corrupt detective? I should follow him.

coyote_side_btl119_0010.mission_info: Dammit! The corrupt detective got away!

coyote_side_m120_0020.mission: Chase the Rumor about People Skipping Town
coyote_side_m120_0020.mission_info: I heard a rumor about a family hustling to flee Ijincho. I should investigate.

coyote_side_m120_0030.mission_info: My guess is that they got bugged at some point. Let's use the detector on their belongings to pinpoint the bug.

coyote_side_btl120_0010.mission_info: Time to make these people regret harassing this family.

coyote_side_m121_0020.mission_info: Looks like Ranpo's got the scent of the corrupt detective, thanks to the cigarette butt he left behind. Is it finally time for our showdown?

coyote_side_m122_0020.mission_info: Tashiro-kun invited me to play Dice & Cube at Paradise VR. He said the first game is free, so I might as well!

coyote_side_m14_0020.mission_info: Something seems to be going on by the soccer field... I wonder if it's some kind of event? I should take a peek.

coyote_side_m14_0030.mission_info: This friendly guy with a crew cut told me about the drone races in town. I should give it a shot.

coyote_side_btl16_0010.mission_info: Man, am I sick of this guy losin' it...

coyote_side_m89_0015.mission: Use Gadgets to Find the Arachnid Man
coyote_side_m89_0015.mission_info: I think I hear the groaning of the Chatter-famous Arachnid Man above me. Gotta try out those gadgets Tsukumo gave me and investigate where the voice is coming from.

coyote_side_m89_0020.mission_info: There's a man hanging on the wall of that apartment building! He looks like he's about to fall... I should help him!

coyote_side_m96_0013.mission: Meet Emily in Front of the Station
coyote_side_m96_0013.mission_info: I invited Emily-chan out to escort her. We're meeting in front of the station.

coyote_side_m96_0045.mission_info: Time to head to Girl's Bite with Emily-chan.

coyote_side_m98_0020.mission: Meet Emily in Front of the Station
coyote_side_m98_0020.mission_info: Emily-chan has something important she wants to talk about. I wonder...

coyote_side_m127_0020.mission: Meet the Client at Hamakita Park
coyote_side_m127_0020.mission_info: Someone shady sent me a challenge. I've got a bad feeling about this... And didn't something like this happen before?

coyote_side_m75_0020.mission_info: Now that I've gathered some info about the phantom ramen stall, I'll go to Meng Wu and share my findings with Joe-san.

coyote_side_m75_0030.mission_info: It sounds crazy, but forming a close bond with some cats is probably the only way to resolve this. Now, where are they? Here, kitty, kitty!

coyote_side_m75_0040.mission_info: As Nekomiya-san said, I'll have to be patient if I want to befriend these cats. I'll find one and spend some time with it to build up our bond, and then I'll be able to find that phantom ramen stall... I hope?

coyote_side_m75_0050.mission_info: I feel like I've gotten pretty close to the cats. I wonder if any of them could guide me to that ramen stall that appears at night?

coyote_side_m75_0060.mission: Witness the Secret of the Ramen Broth
coyote_side_m75_0060.mission_info: The final touch on this ramen broth shall be...!

coyote_side_btl92_0010.mission_info: Absolutely no reselling, or I'll beat the snot outta you!

coyote_side_m95_0020.mission_info: I should meet up with Tsukino-chan at our usual place. We're meeting at night this time, though.

coyote_side_btl102_0010.mission_info: Kazamiya is using an extract. Well, two can play at that game.

coyote_side_m123_0020.mission_info: I hear there've been some upgrades to VR Sugoroku. Let's play a game!

coyote_side_m123_0030.mission: Defeat the Rivals in VR Sugoroku
coyote_side_m123_0030.mission_info: According to Tashiro-kun, I might see some characters who will "surprise" me. I'm looking forward to it!

coyote_side_m124_0020.mission_info: To help Iyama-san and Professor Yoshikawa with their research, I need to collect the ingredients for their extracts. Iyama-san said he'd reward me with new extract recipes when I do. I think he needed Roses?

coyote_side_btl121_0010.mission_info: To think he was the corrupt detective this whole time...

coyote_side_btl127_0010.mission_info: This guy's gotta be pretty tough. I can't let my guard down!

coyote_m04_01200.mission: Find the Spot Where the Body Was Found
coyote_m04_01200.mission_info: Mikoshiba's body was discovered somewhere in this building. Apparently it was badly decomposed, so there must be traces left somewhere...

coyote_side_m03_0050.mission: Track the Perverts Who Escaped to Kamurocho
coyote_side_m03_0050.mission_info: Four notorious perverts have escaped prison and are hiding somewhere in Kamurocho. I should learn about them in the Buzz Researcher so I can track them down.

coyote_side_m03_0060.mission_info: Chatter about Professor Panty was sent from Tender. I should go there to ask about it.

coyote_side_m03_0070.mission_info: If I want to catch him, I need to know what type of underwear Professor Panty likes. Which means... I need to ask Mari about her panties...

coyote_side_m03_0110.mission: Track the Perverts Who Escaped to Kamurocho
coyote_side_m03_0110.mission_info: Professor Panty got away, but there are plenty of other perverts. I should round them up!

coyote_side_m03_0115.mission_info: What do I even say to her?

coyote_side_g03_0030.mission_info:
All right, I found out where Judge Creep 'n Peep was last seen.
He supposedly shows up at night. Better go check it out.

coyote_side_m03_0150.mission_info: Judge Creep 'n Peep now has camouflage, and he can blend into the background! If it's going to be too hard to find him with my eyes alone, then I might need to try something different.

coyote_side_m03_0180.mission_info: The perverts kidnapped Tsukino-chan, and I need to meet Yosuke-kun at the Kamuro Theater at night...

coyote_side_m03_0190.mission_info: I need to find out where Tsukino-chan was taken. The only clue I have is her bag...

coyote_side_g03_0040.mission: Find a Place to Sneak In
coyote_side_g03_0040.mission_info: They took Tsukino-chan into this building. Maybe there's a spot where I can sneak in at night.

coyote_side_btl03_0030.mission_info: You guys should go back to prison.

coyote_side_m51_0020.mission: Talk to Amasawa at the MRC
coyote_side_m51_0020.mission_info: Seems like Amasawa wants to talk to me about the teacher who got hit by a ball in the hallway. I'll swing by the MRC later to hear her out.

coyote_side_m51_0025.mission: Talk to Amasawa at the MRC
coyote_side_m51_0025.mission_info: It seems that Amasawa wants to talk to me about the teacher who got hit by the ball in the hallway. I'll swing by the MRC again to hear about it.

coyote_side_m51_0030.mission: Talk to Ebisu-sensei in the Faculty Room
coyote_side_m51_0030.mission_info: I'm going to stand guard for Ebisu-sensei because those delinquent kids keep pulling pranks on him. For now, I should go talk to him in the faculty room.

coyote_side_g51_0010.mission: Find the Traps Set for Ebisu-sensei
coyote_side_g51_0010.mission_info: Seems like there are traps waiting for Ebisu-sensei in his classroom. Better find them all before he starts his class.

coyote_side_m51_0040.mission_info: I should warn Ebisu-sensei about the traps.

coyote_side_g51_0020.mission: Find the Traps Set for Ebisu-sensei
coyote_side_g51_0020.mission_info: While I'm searching for the traps they set up for Ebisu-sensei, I'm going to be extra mindful of any traps that are only there to distract me.

coyote_side_m51_0067.mission_info: I need to go after Ebisu-sensei. I'm getting a bad feeling about this!

coyote_side_g51_0030.mission: Find the Traps Set for Ebisu-sensei
coyote_side_g51_0030.mission_info: Those little brats set up more traps. I'll find them so Ebisu-sensei remains unharmed.

coyote_side_m050_015.mission_info: Ask the trio for details about the time capsule.

coyote_side_m050_020.mission: Find the "Giant's Wheel" & "Tree With the Most Branches"
coyote_side_m050_020.mission_info: I need to find something that's been compared to a "giant's wheel glaring at the tree with the most branches." Then it was three steps south, two steps east, and there the time capsule lies.

coyote_side_m050_030.mission_info: Hand over the time capsule to the clients.

coyote_side_m050_040.mission_info: Let's confirm the contents of the time capsule.

coyote_side_m050_045.mission_info: Need to find Goto-san in Chinatown.

coyote_side_m050_050.mission: Talk to the Woman Who Looks Like Goto
coyote_side_m050_050.mission_info: I found someone who fits Goto-san's description but with a few differences, which might just be from the fact she's older than she was in the sketch. But what if I have the wrong person? I'll call out to her...

coyote_side_m01_020.mission: Meet the Client at their Office in Kamurocho
coyote_side_m01_020.mission_info: The client's office is on the third floor of a building on Tenkaichi Street. Time to head over.

coyote_side_m01_035.mission: Question the Members of Kazuto Jumonji
coyote_side_m01_035.mission_info: The Kazuto Jumonji might've seen something suspicious. Better find out.

coyote_side_m01_040.mission: Talk to Sanada on the Rooftop
coyote_side_m01_040.mission_info: A Kazuto Jumonji member, Sanada-san, is up on the rooftop. Time to have ourselves a chat.

coyote_side_m01_045.mission_info: It seems Sanada-san did notice something suspicious, but he's too hesitant to say anything. Guess I'll just have to ask.

coyote_side_m01_050.mission_info: I should head back to the office.

coyote_side_m01_055.mission_info: Apparently there's an odor of unknown origin here. No better time for him when it comes to smells.

coyote_side_g03_0020.mission_info: All right, I found out where Ass Catchem was last seen. I should go there and find him.

coyote_side_m03_0120.mission: Track the Perverts Who Escaped to Kamurocho
coyote_side_m03_0120.mission_info: Four infamous perverts have escaped and are now roaming the streets of Kamurocho. Better collect some info from the Buzz Researcher and catch these pervs.

coyote_side_m03_0215.mission_info: Tsukino-chan's inside this place somewhere. I'll have to search every nook and cranny!

coyote_side_m16_0020.mission_info: Sounds like God-Tier Games is almost done with their latest project. I should meet Okizaki in front of the Industrial Hall Building.

coyote_drama_m11_010.mission: Meet Up with Kento at Hamakita Park at Night
coyote_drama_m11_010.mission_info: Apparently the biker gangs hang around Hamakita Park at night. Kento-kun's bringing me a motorcycle, so I should meet up with him.

coyote_drama_m11_090.mission: Head to the Death Race from the Garage
coyote_drama_m11_090.mission_info: Looks like I have to race against some Made In Heaven guys. I should head to the Death Race from the Garage.

coyote_drama_m11_310.mission: Investigate Bomber, Near South Sakura River Street
coyote_drama_m11_310.mission_info: Bomber apparently lives around the homeless camp by South Sakura River Street. I should try to look him up before the race.

coyote_drama_m11_320.mission_info: Where's Bomber going? I should follow him without letting him notice me...

coyote_drama_m11_330.mission_info: Bomber had an argument with his girlfriend. There might've been an important reason for it... I should just ask her what happened.

coyote_drama_m11_340.mission: Beat Bomber in the Death Race
coyote_drama_m11_340.mission_info: I'm going to beat Bomber in a death race and make him leave Made In Heaven. That way he can follow his heart to Hiyori-san!

coyote_drama_m11_430.mission_info: I beat Bomber! So now the next step is...

coyote_drama_m12_010.mission_info: After the Bakuon Rairyu, I'm going up against the Raging Angels.

coyote_drama_m12_310.mission: Beat Rina Minagawa in the Death Race
coyote_drama_m12_310.mission_info: I'm finally going up against Rina Minagawa of the Raging Angels, and I'm gonna win!

coyote_drama_m12_410.mission_info: I beat Rina Minagawa. Next up is...

coyote_drama_m14_310.mission: Beat Suou in the Death Race
coyote_drama_m14_310.mission_info: Finally, it's time to race Suou. I really can't lose this one!

coyote_drama_m14_440.mission_info: Suou's in a total frenzy. Guess I need to calm him down.

coyote_side_m75_0010.mission_info: I want to find out as much as I can about that phantom ramen stall. Joe-san would like that, I bet. Well, I could start by putting an ear out for rumors, either around town or on Chatter.

coyote_side_g89_0020.mission_info: The man named Tamai claims he was just birdwatching. Sounds pretty fishy to me... I should watch him to see if there's anything suspicious about him.

side_btl89_0010.mission_info: Tamai was a panty thief. Gotta calm him down, however possible.

coyote_side_m92_0015.mission_info: Sugiura bought the same skateboard twice by mistake. He wants me to buy one off him, but he wants 10,000 yen for it...

coyote_side_g92_0010.mission_info: I need to get to Ebisu Pawn before the reseller gets there! I've got three minutes.

coyote_side_m73_0085.mission: Find the UFO on Seiryo's Roof
coyote_side_m73_0085.mission_info: So many students out here trying to spot the UFO. I should keep my eyes peeled and observe them closely.

coyote_drama_m51_020.mission: Head to the Photography Club Room
coyote_drama_m51_020.mission_info: I'll be helping Toribe, the photography club's president, by taking photos of the delinquent students. I can start by going to the photography club room on the 3rd floor of the training building.

coyote_drama_m51_025.mission: Head Out with Toribe to Photograph a Delinquent Student
coyote_drama_m51_025.mission_info: Our first target is supposedly a pickpocketing, troublemaking student. First thing to do is talk to Toribe.

coyote_drama_g51_010.mission_info: Okay. Time to tail Fujimaru and make sure I'm not seen.

coyote_drama_g51_015.mission_info: I want to capture the moment when Fujimaru picks a pocket, with an evil look on his face.

coyote_drama_m51_070.mission: Make an Appearance at the Photography Club Later
coyote_drama_m51_070.mission_info: I have a bad feeling about letting that Toribe girl just roam around. I'd like to check on her.
