coyote_drama_m31_310.mission_info: I should keep training at the gym until I'm able to spar Oshikiri again.

coyote_drama_m32_010.mission_info: I should keep training at the gym until I'm able to spar Oshikiri again.

coyote_drama_m33_200.mission_info: I should keep training at the gym until I'm able to spar Oshikiri again.

coyote_drama_m34_200.mission_info: Todoroki's putting together a special counter-Kenya training program for me. I should give it my best so I can win against Oshikiri.

side_m65_0030.mission: Head to Hyakkei Street, Where Hakase Is
side_m65_0030.mission_info: Hakase-san called me and said she's being watched. I need to meet her at Hyakkei Street right away!

coyote_drama_m11_005.mission: Talk to Amasawa at the MRC
coyote_drama_m11_005.mission_info: Amasawa mentioned that she has a new undercover job. Before dealing with my other investigations, I'll go see what that's about.

coyote_drama_m91_015.mission: Talk to Amasawa at the MRC
coyote_drama_m91_015.mission_info: I wonder if they've gotten any closer to finding a lead on the Professor? I should catch up with Amasawa sometime during the day.

coyote_dlc_g01_010.mission_info: That dirty detective stole the voice recorder and took off! I gotta catch his ass!

coyote_dlc_btl01_010.mission_info: Time to teach Senda and his goons a lesson.

coyote_dlc_m01_00600.mission_info: I'll swing by Tender for some drinks and see if I can find any work. Masuda might have something for me.

coyote_dlc_m01_00910.mission_info: Doing work'll help get my mind off things. I'll see if Masuda has anything for me. He'll probably be pissed I turned down such a big job.

coyote_dlc_m01_01000.mission_info: Higashi, that sneaky bastard. Bet he called 'cause he was worried about me. Can't say I'm thrilled about having to babysit some kid, but this could be exactly what I need right now. Gotta stay busy.

coyote_DLC_btl01_020.mission_info: Time to shut down these clowns.

coyote_dlc_g02_010.mission_info: Hotta's story straight up contradicts that woman's story. So what the hell happened here? Gotta examine the scene and figure out which one of them is right.

coyote_dlc_btl02_010.mission_info: Mikiko's in trouble again? Guess it's my job to clean up her shit.

coyote_dlc_m02_00500.mission_info: Mikiko was a regular at Café Alps. Think I'll ask around there for now and see what I can learn.

coyote_dlc_m02_00750.mission_info: If Mikiko's alive, then she might've come here. And if she did, someone could've seen her. Wonder if anyone here knows anything.

coyote_dlc_g02_015.mission: Find a Way to Wake Up the Manager
coyote_dlc_g02_015.mission_info: The Café Alps manager is out cold. Gotta be some way to wake him up. I'll take a look around and see what I can find.

coyote_dlc_m02_00800.mission: Talk to the Café Alps Manager
coyote_dlc_m02_00800.mission_info: Well, that was a pain, but he's finally awake. Now it's time to find out if he saw Mikiko.

coyote_dlc_btl02_020.mission_info: These guys're pissing me off. I don't have time for this shit.

coyote_dlc_m02_01100.mission_info: Momoko's is in the Champion District. Momoko and Mikiko are old friends, so maybe she knows something about Mikiko.

coyote_dlc_btl02_030.mission_info: Jun's out cold. Gotta take care of these thugs first before I can help him out.

coyote_dlc_m02_01300.mission_info: Didn't expect to have to deal with that. Anyway, on to Momoko-chan's bar.

coyote_dlc_m02_01410.mission_info: Anyone who's been coming here for at least a month might know something.

coyote_dlc_m02_01420.mission_info: According to the girl at the café, the old cleaning lady might've seen Mikiko. She's apparently in the garden on the roof of Kamuro Theater.

coyote_dlc_m02_01425.mission_info: I don't see the cleaning lady, so might as well see what this little girl's deal is. She's looking for a "Miki-chan." Think she might be lost.

coyote_dlc_m02_01430.mission_info: The little girl who lost her cat said the cleaning lady went over to the Millennium Tower.

coyote_dlc_m02_01440.mission: Find a Way to Get the Cat Down
coyote_dlc_m02_01440.mission_info: The cleaning lady's too focused on that cat to pay me any attention. If I can find some way to get it down to safety, maybe she'll finally hear me out.

coyote_dlc_m02_01500.mission_info: Hopefully she'll listen to me now.

coyote_dlc_btl02_040.mission_info: Can't believe those Bato idiots would stoop to kidnapping. Time to knock some sense into 'em.

coyote_dlc_m02_01800.mission_info: Those Bato bastards took Jun. Maybe searching their office'll give me some idea of where they took him.

coyote_dlc_g02_020.mission_info: There's gotta be something here that'll lead to where they're keeping Jun.

coyote_dlc_m02_01900.mission: Head to the Bato's New Hideout

coyote_dlc_g02_030.mission_info: Gotta find Jun before they find me.

coyote_dlc_btl02_050.mission_info: This guy's ex-Omi Alliance, huh? Sure looks the part. This ain't gonna be easy.

coyote_dlc_m02_02300.mission: Find a Way to Lose the Pursuer
coyote_dlc_m02_02300.mission_info: One of those Bato guys is tailing me. I can't meet up with Jun like this. But... I think I've got just the disguise that can help.

coyote_dlc_m02_02600.mission_info: I could really use a break after all that.

coyote_dlc_m02_02750.mission: Inspect the Office with the Drone
coyote_dlc_m02_02750.mission_info: Someone might be hiding in the office. Let's see what the drone spots.

coyote_dlc_g03_010.mission_info: Shirakaba was lying. He definitely knows about Mikiko. Must be something about her in this room I can find.

coyote_dlc_btl03_010.mission_info: Don't know who these Crimson Lotus goons are, but they don't look like they're here to chat.

coyote_dlc_btl03_020.mission_info: Can't let my guard down around this guy. He's one tough bastard.

coyote_dlc_a03_050.mission_info: There's a fire on Tenkaichi Street, not to mention someone got killed. Better go check it out!

coyote_dlc_m03_01000.mission: Reach the Fire from the Back Alley
coyote_dlc_m03_01000.mission_info: I should be able to get up to the roof of the building that Mikiko was in from behind the Nightlife Info Booth!

coyote_dlc_btl03_030.mission_info: Get the hell outta my way!

coyote_dlc_m03_01400.mission_info: I should check out that torched building and see if I can find some clues about Mikiko there.

coyote_dlc_m03_01500.mission: Reach the Fire from the Back Alley
coyote_dlc_m03_01500.mission_info: To sneak into the burnt building, I'll probably need to find a way in from behind the Nightlife Info Booth.

coyote_dlc_g03_012.mission_info: Can't waste time dealing with the cops. Gotta be sneaky.

coyote_dlc_g03_015.mission_info: No time to be stealthy—I need clues.

coyote_dlc_m03_02000.mission_info: Mikiko may target Kenmochi next. She might show up if I stake out his office.

coyote_dlc_g03_020.mission_info: Gotta make sure he doesn't see me.

coyote_dlc_btl03_050.mission_info: They took Mikiko, but I'm comin' to get her back.

coyote_dlc_btl04_010.mission_info: I don't know what's going on, but if they won't tell me where Mikiko is, then I'll just beat it out of 'em.

coyote_dlc_m04_00620.mission_info: I wanna go back to the office and tell Jun what's up before I head to Ijincho.

coyote_dlc_m04_00650.mission: Head to the Bato Detective Agency When Ready
coyote_dlc_m04_00650.mission_info: I should show Jun around Kamurocho while I have the chance. Don't know what might happen in Ijincho, after all. I'll head to the Bato Detective Agency when I'm done.

coyote_dlc_g04_010.mission: Infiltrate the Party With a Disguise
coyote_dlc_g04_010.mission_info: Looks like I'll need a disguise to sneak into the party, but what? Might find a hint somewhere if I look around.

coyote_dlc_m04_01060.mission_info: A waiter won't have any problems going in and out of the party. There's apparently some waiter slacking off in the smoking area. Let's see if I can't get him to part with his uniform.

coyote_dlc_btl04_015.mission_info: I knew this would happen. Well, guess I gotta mug him. Y'know, with this kinda luck getting mugged, maybe Tashiro should buy himself a lottery ticket. Or, uh, maybe not.

coyote_dlc_m04_01100.mission_info: I've got my disguise, and I'm ready to party.

coyote_dlc_m04_01150.mission: Search for Mikiko and Kyoya Sadamoto
coyote_dlc_m04_01150.mission_info: Gotta ask around and find out if anyone's seen Mikiko or Kyoya Sadamoto.

coyote_dlc_m04_01400.mission_info: Mikiko was seen heading to the bathroom. Maybe she's going after Crimson Lotus when they're alone.

coyote_dlc_btl04_020.mission_info: Don't have time for this shit!

coyote_dlc_btl04_040.mission: Defend Your Honor with Your Fists
coyote_dlc_btl04_040.mission_info: This is the one fight I can't afford to lose.

coyote_dlc_m02_02300a.mission_info: Perfect. Now to meet up with Jun at the Batting Center.

coyote_dlc_m02_01400.mission_info: Momoko-chan gave me some solid advice. Guess I'll head to Kamuro Theater since Mikiko and I have some history there.

coyote_dlc_m04_01850.mission: Take a Taxi to the Shirakaba Clinic
coyote_dlc_m04_01850.mission_info: Shirakaba challenged me to a duel. He and I need to have a chat about what Mikiko wants for her own future. But first, I gotta make sure I'm ready. Once I am, I'll take a taxi to his place.

coyote_dlc_m03_02150.mission_info: They took Mikiko, but I'm comin' to get her back.
